			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Whistleblower reveals Big Pharma pressures researchers to only release &quot;positive&quot;
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1859783">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Big Pharma is pretty fucked up because they are:<br />
<br />
1. Near willingly Incompetant. <br />
2. Uninnovative.<br />
3. Greedy.<br />
<br />
All because of IP issues surrounding the formulation and creation process of the drug. The way IP is handled like currency in contracts for testing or manufacturing is absurdly arcane and complicated, and it mires these business processes in ways that make you roll your eyes. <br />
<br />
Of course, my job was to say that excessive regulation is to blame, but the real truth is that the research investments for companies are best categorized as outsourced contracts rather than in house expenses for investors. That's what I focused on, and the structure of regulation is more something that is just going to be there to deal with because we aren't China.<br />
<br />
Investors are killing everything because they are all shortsighted mooks.<br />
<br />
IP in this industry is disgusting.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
